ackModal_main_2526008\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 15, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bem1665703174291.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bem1665703174291.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bem1665703174291.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bem1665703174291\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The security driver control structure is used to exchange information between the driver and the caller.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bem1665703174291__section_w2059ab1b5b1_w2060ab1b5_w2061ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1095277e49\">Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bem1665703174291__p_d131996e1_d131997e1_d131998e1\">The security driver structure contains some members that are reserved for Uniface use only, and must not be used.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bem1665703174291__section_w2062ab1b5b3_w2063ab1b5_w2064ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1095277e58\">\n                       \n Members\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bem1665703174291__p_d132002e1_d132003e1_d132004e1\">The following table lists the members of the structure that can be used by the security driver.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"5\" id=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Security Driver Structure Members</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__1\">\n Type\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__2\">\n Name\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__3\">\n Description\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__4\">\n C/S\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__5\">\n SMTP\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">void *</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">DrvArea</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__3\">\n Can be used by the implementation to allocate memory for driver-specific information or state, and store the pointer. The implementation is responsible for freeing any memory that it allocates.\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__4\">\n X\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__5\">\n X\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">unsigned char *</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Username</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__3\">\n Points to the start of the null-terminated user name.\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__4\">\n X\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__5\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">unsigned char *</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Passwd</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__3\">\n Points to the start of the null-terminated user password.\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__4\">\n X\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__5\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">unsigned char *</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">NewPasswd</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__3\">\n Points to the start of the null-terminated user new password.\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__4\">\n X\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__5\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">void *</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">UserToken</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__3\">Points to a user token, required on Microsoft\n                        Windows platforms to create a process for the given (authenticated) user. </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__4\">\n X\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__5\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">unsigned char *</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">InBuf</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__3\">\n Points to the start of the input buffer, that contains the information to be encoded or decoded.\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__4\">\n X\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__5\">\n X\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">int</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">InBufLen</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__3\">Length (in bytes) of the buffer pointed to by\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">InBuf</code>. </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__4\">\n X\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__5\">\n X\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">int</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">InDataLen</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__3\">Length (in bytes) of the data stored in the\n                        buffer pointed to by <code class=\"ph codeph\">InBuf</code>. </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__4\">\n X\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__5\">\n X\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">unsigned char *</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">OutBuf</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__3\">Points to the start of the output buffer, that\n                        contains the result of encoding or decoding the data in the input buffer\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">InBuf</code>. </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__4\">\n X\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__5\">\n X\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">int</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">OutBufLen</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__3\">Length (in bytes) of the buffer pointed to by\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">OutBuf</code>. </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__4\">\n X\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__5\">\n X\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">int</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">OutDataLen</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__3\">Length (in bytes) of the data stored in the\n                        buffer pointed to by <code class=\"ph codeph\">OutBuf</code>. </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__4\">\n X\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__5\">\n X\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">unsigned char *</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">ErrMsg</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__3\">Points to the buffer containing the\n                        implementation-specific error text (or info message text) that describes the\n                        supplied error number (or info message number) contained in\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">Error</code>. This buffer is guaranteed to be at least 256\n                        bytes. </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__4\">\n X\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__5\">\n X\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">int</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">ErrMsgLen</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__3\">Length (in bytes) of the\n                        implementation-specific error text (or info message text) in the buffer\n                        pointed to by <code class=\"ph codeph\">ErrMsg</code>. </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__4\">\n X\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__5\">\n X\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">long</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Error</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__3\">\n Implementation-specific error message number (or info message number) returned by the security driver.\n <p class=\"p\">If it encounters an error, it should also return a status from the entry point function indicating the severity of the error. This member is only viewed when the entry point function return status is not successful (not <code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_SUCCESS</code>). It is this number for which text must be supplied in the <code class=\"ph codeph\">ErrMsg</code> buffer.</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__4\">\n X\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__5\">\n X\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">unsigned char *</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Function</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__3\"> Specifies the action to be taken by the\n                        security driver, as listed in Security Driver Functions. </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__4\">\n X\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__5\">\n X\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">unsigned char *</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Properties</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__3\">SMTP driver characteristics, provided in the\n                        first parameter of the <code class=\"ph codeph\">SetSecurity</code> operation of the\n                        UPOPMAIL component. It consists of a Uniface list containing the following\n                        keyword-value pairs: <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bem1665703174291__li_d47249e1_d47250e1_d47251e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">SMTP=<var class=\"keyword varname\">EntryPointFunction</var>\n</code>—function that implements the SMTP security driver; can be\n                              upper or lowercase, and is case-sensitive. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bem1665703174291__li_d47252e1_d47253e1_d47254e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">USE=</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">OPT</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">MAND</code>—indicates whether use of\n                              this driver is optional or mandatory <p class=\"p\">OPT—optional, if the server\n                                 supports this functionality;</p>\n<p class=\"p\">MAND—mandatory (default); if the server does not support it, an\n                                 error must be returned.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\">The keyword and values may be upper or lower case. This string is in the\n                           UTF-8 character set.</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__4\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__5\">\n X\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">unsigned char *</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Parameters</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__3\">SMTP driver-specific parameters, provided in\n                        the second parameter of the <code class=\"ph codeph\">SetSecurity</code> operation of the\n                        UPOPMAIL component. It consists of a Uniface list in the UTF-8 character\n                        set. See the documentation for a specific driver for the keywords and values\n                        that may be present. <p class=\"p\">Drivers can always use the <code class=\"ph codeph\">DrvArea</code>\n                           member to allocate space for their own administrations. The pointer is\n                           preserved over calls and it is the driver's responsibility to free the\n                           memory.</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__4\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bem1665703174291__table_d15749e1_d15750e1_d15751e1__entry__5\">\n X\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rsn1665703174361.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Security Driver Functions</a><p>A security driver must perform the action requested of it, as defined by the Function member of the USecDrv structure. Some actions are applicable to both client/server and SMTP security drivers, others are specific to one or the other.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526008\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526008\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Security Driver Control Structure (USecDrv) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 15, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 The security driver control structure is used to exchange information between the driver and the caller. Description The security driver structure contains some members that are reserved for Uniface use only, and must not be used. Members The following table lists the members of the structure that can be used by the security driver. Table 1. Security Driver Structure Members Type Name Description C/S SMTP void * DrvArea Can be used by the implementation to allocate memory for driver-specific information or state, and store the pointer. The implementation is responsible for freeing any memory that it allocates. X X unsigned char * Username Points to the start of the null-terminated user name. X unsigned char * Passwd Points to the start of the null-terminated user password. X unsigned char * NewPasswd Points to the start of the null-terminated user new password. X void * UserToken Points to a user token, required on Microsoft Windows platforms to create a process for the given (authenticated) user. X unsigned char * InBuf Points to the start of the input buffer, that contains the information to be encoded or decoded. X X int InBufLen Length (in bytes) of the buffer pointed to by InBuf . X X int InDataLen Length (in bytes) of the data stored in the buffer pointed to by InBuf . X X unsigned char * OutBuf Points to the start of the output buffer, that contains the result of encoding or decoding the data in the input buffer InBuf . X X int OutBufLen Length (in bytes) of the buffer pointed to by OutBuf . X X int OutDataLen Length (in bytes) of the data stored in the buffer pointed to by OutBuf . X X unsigned char * ErrMsg Points to the buffer containing the implementation-specific error text (or info message text) that describes the supplied error number (or info message number) contained in Error . This buffer is guaranteed to be at least 256 bytes. X X int ErrMsgLen Length (in bytes) of the implementation-specific error text (or info message text) in the buffer pointed to by ErrMsg . X X long Error Implementation-specific error message number (or info message number) returned by the security driver. If it encounters an error, it should also return a status from the entry point function indicating the severity of the error. This member is only viewed when the entry point function return status is not successful (not USEC_SUCCESS ). It is this number for which text must be supplied in the ErrMsg buffer. X X unsigned char * Function Specifies the action to be taken by the security driver, as listed in Security Driver Functions. X X unsigned char * Properties SMTP driver characteristics, provided in the first parameter of the SetSecurity operation of the UPOPMAIL component. It consists of a Uniface list containing the following keyword-value pairs: SMTP= EntryPointFunction —function that implements the SMTP security driver; can be upper or lowercase, and is case-sensitive. USE= OPT | MAND —indicates whether use of this driver is optional or mandatory OPT—optional, if the server supports this functionality; MAND—mandatory (default); if the server does not support it, an error must be returned. The keyword and values may be upper or lower case. This string is in the UTF-8 character set. X unsigned char * Parameters SMTP driver-specific parameters, provided in the second parameter of the SetSecurity operation of the UPOPMAIL component. It consists of a Uniface list in the UTF-8 character set. See the documentation for a specific driver for the keywords and values that may be present. Drivers can always use the DrvArea member to allocate space for their own administrations. The pointer is preserved over calls and it is the driver's responsibility to free the memory. X Related Links Security Driver Functions A security driver must perform the action requested of it, as defined by the Function member of the USecDrv structure. Some actions are applicable to both client/server and SMTP security drivers, others are specific to one or the other. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}